  "articleSummary": "This article argues that sustainable collaboration relies on four structural pillars—Safety, Speed, Clarity, and Commitment—which together foster psychological safety and accelerate iterative decision-making. Targeted at engineering, product, and cross-functional teams, it provides pragmatic guidelines for establishing explicit team norms, setting role-specific expectations, and using clear status labels to streamline feedback loops. Written in a direct, tutorial-style tone, the piece frames collaboration as an intentional system where a \"culture of error\" and early, low-stakes prototyping replace rigid perfectionism. By treating draft proposals as a \"fountain of opportunities\" and measuring success through idea velocity and team vulnerability, the author emphasizes consistent modeling of collaborative behaviors over formalized processes.",
